cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the spread of wireless worms through mobile devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and wireless networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of human mobility patterns on epidemic spread, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of Bluetooth-enabled smart phones for proximity attacks could also fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
